			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Hazardous waste treatment involves the collection, treatment, and disposal of waste material that, when improperly handled, can cause substantial harm to human health and safety or to the environment. Hazardous waste is generated from many sources and may come in many forms, including liquids, solids gases, and sludges. It is commonly stored prior to treatment or disposal, and must be stored in containers, tanks, containment buildings, drip pads, waste piles, or surface impoundments that comply with the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act (RCRA) regulations.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">危险废物处理涉及废料的收集、处理和处置，如果处理不当，会对人类健康和安全或环境造成重大危害。危险废物产生于多种来源，并可能以多种形式出现，包括液体、固体气体和淤泥。危险废物通常在处理或处置前进行储存，并且必须储存在符合《资源保护和回收法》（RCRA）规定的容器、储罐、隔离建筑、滴水垫、废物堆或地表蓄水池中。</common:generalComment>
